title: For Sale:  Walther/Smith Wesson 99 Compact .40sw
postcontent:
Guys,
I am selling my Smith and Wesson 99 Compact in .40sw.
The gun is in excellent condition and has less than 200 rounds thru it.  I just had the slide coated in Cerakote Graphite Black, picked it up this week.  It looks fantastic.   The frame is in great shape.  Overall the pistol is in excellent cosmetic and  functional condition.  

Let's be very clear...the SW99C is virtually identical to the Walther P99C.  The primary difference is the Walther has a square trigger guard and the SW99C has the rounded trigger guard.  This model is a very early production one.  What this means is that it has the very desirable Walther Made frame (German built) and it is stamped "Made in Germany".  The slide is the only part stamped Smith and Wesson.  Later models were made entirely by Smith.  This model has the AS (anti stress) two stage trigger and it's very nice and very smooth.  

Pistol comes with two genuine Walther Mags both are 8 round.  One has the finger rest, the other is flush fit.  

Price is $450.  No trades, sorry.  I prefer cash, but I can take Visa/MC but it's 2.5% more to cover fees.  Msg me with any questions.  I will ship but only to an FFL and I must have a copy of the FFL holders license before I will ship.
Don

The bluing is basically 100%, as is the condition of the stock. (Has original buttplate as well) Could of even be re blued way back when. I cant believe how minty it all is. Shoots perfect and is beyond accurate. No pitting or rust . Few minor scratches on stock. You would have no idea this gun was from the 30s!. This is a real find. 

What makes this rifle extra special is that it was made in a short run of these that werent made with a serial number on them (somtime in the 1930's). This increases its desirability to collectors and value by quite a bit. No dros or ffl transfer is necessary for this gem. Cash and carry ( this is just about the only scenario you can still do this) 
This Rifle isnt just a safe queen or a wall hanger ,, if youre looking for a perfect shooting .22 bolt this will fit the bill and definitely last many generations to come! 

was quoted by a collector this thing could easily go for 5-600$ for this run of the model 69a and its condition. So send me fair trades with pics!

Must meet face to face in orange county. 

Only interested in trades! Make an offer
